<L>__{interior m.c.i. walpole visiting area 1989 day}
<A>__{superimpose: four years later visiting day. inmates sit across from their families. mirtha is sitting at the glass. george walks to his seat.}
<C>__{mirtha}
<D>__{i'm divorcing you, george. i'm getting custody of kristina. and when you get out next week, you're going to pay support and that's the end of it. alright? there's someone else. i'm sorry.}
<A>__{george just looks at her. his face is stone. but he is moved.}
<C>__{mirtha }
<D>__{you should have taken better care of me, you know? you've been away a long time. four years. say something.}
