<D>__{what do you want me to say? i'm in prison. you should know. you put me here.}
<C>__{mirtha}
<D>__{fuck you, george. i knew you'd say something like that. always thinking about yourself.}
<A>__{she moves away and drags nine year old kristina into the room. kristina yanks her arm away and they get into a heated argument. through the glass, george can't hear the words but it's clear that kristina doesn't want to be here.}
<C>__{george}
<D>__{my baby. she's so big.}
<A>__{mirtha forces kristina over to the glass and keeps showing her, prompting her to talk. kristina stares at george through the glass. cool. defiant. angry. she picks up the phone and speaks, every word an accusation.}
